== SOURCE

https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-017-00626-6
https://astronomy.com/news/2016/08/how-does-mars-rover-curiositys-new-ai-system-work
https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=6879

== AGENT

NASA

== GOAL

To allow the mars rover Curiosity to select desired rocks and soil targets for analysis

== DATA

not specifed

== METHODS

NASA use a AI system called AEGIS which uses an algorithm called ROCKSTER to look for enclosed boundary contours in objects

== RESULTS

The AI system has an accuracy of 93%

== ISSUES

No issues

== SCORE

9

== COMMENTS

This was a very interesting application of Machine Learning. Having an autonomous robot such as Curiosity to find rocks and soil allows use to make advances in our knowledge of other Planets from the comfort of Earth.  
